            "note": "cache-hit input $0.30/M; Kimi API public token pricing; Kimi Code subscription billing, entitlement, and live quota remain separate; 1M context; reasoning_effort supports low/high/max; the Kimi API pricing page documents API default max, while the current Kimi Code model page documents default high, so the effective Kimi Code default is not inferred; official Limitations (moonshot-kimi-k3-blog): (1) trained in preserved-thinking-history mode, so generation quality can become highly unstable if the agent harness drops historical thinking content or if a session is switched to K3 mid-stream from another model — run K3 in a verified-compatible harness (Kimi Code) on a fresh session and never a mid-session model switch; (2) tuned for long-horizon tasks and over-proactive under ambiguity, so on minor issues or ambiguous intent it may make unexpected decisions on the user's behalf — set explicit behavioral boundaries in the system prompt or AGENTS.md when tight guardrails are required; (3) noticeable user-experience gap vs Claude Fable 5 and GPT-5.6 Sol; vendor-published benchmarks are not imported into this registry and independent cross-vendor verification remains unknown"
